Kim Jong Il inspects military academy
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected the military academy of tankmen and automobile drivers.
He was accompanied by director of the KPA general political department Jo Myong Rok, chief of the general staff Kim Yong Chun, Minister of the People's Armed Forces Kim Il Chol, secretary Kim Kuk Thae and first vice department director Jang Song Thaek of the Worker's Party of Korea Central Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He looked round the monument to the on-site instructions of the President Kim Il Sung and the revolutionary history education room. He said the President's immortal feats are brilliantly recorded in the history of building the Korean People's Army.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He went to military affairs study rooms to learn how education was given.
   In order to train cadets into competent commanding officers of armored and other vehicle drivers, equipped with deep knowledge of military affairs and high commanding ability, practical education and visual aid education should be strengthened and the contents of education be steadily improved to meet the demands of the developing situation, he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He went round cultural, educational and logistic facilities and taught ways of supplying larger quantities of delicious non-staple food to the cadets.
   He inspected the inside and outside of the academy and urged military educational institutions to take the lead in implementing the party's line and policy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He noted with great satisfaction that the teaching staff of the academy had improved the educational and cultural conditions of the academy and devotedly worked to train commanding officers and experts in the sector of armored and other vehicles. And he highly appreciated their feats.   He had a picture taken with the teaching staff of the academy.

NDFSK publishes declaration of struggle
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- The central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) published a declaration of struggle on May 13 on the occasion of the 19th anniversary of the heroic Kwangju Popular Uprising, according to radio Voice of National Salvation from Seoul.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The declaration said that the Kwangju people's resistance in May 1980 was a new milestone which brought about switchover toward anti-U.S. independence in the history of the people's movement and a bloody resistance which demonstrated the heroic stamina and fighting spirit of the Korean people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It called for turning out in the May all-out struggle, holding higher the blood-stained banner of the Kwangju people's resistance.
   It called for concentrating all efforts on the nationwide struggle to topple the traitorous Kim Dae Jung "government" that is driving the people into the jaws of death, not content with leaving one half of the country lock, stock and barrel to the mercy of outside forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It went on :   Without the powerful anti-U.S. struggle to oust the United States, neither independence and democratization of society nor the reunification of the nation can be achieved. 
This is a lesson of the Kwangju resistance and a sum-total of the anti-fascist struggle for democratization.   It also called for putting an end to the U.S. colonial domination and intervention through the anti-U.S. struggle.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The present crafty and atrocious "government" is resorting to suppression on one hand and appeasement on the other in a bid to dampen the people's May fighting spirit, it said. This is no more than the last-ditch effort of the weaker driven into a tight corner.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It called for confidently taking the initiative in the political situation and leading the struggle to victory in the spirit of the May all-out struggle. It appealed to bring earlier the bright dawn of independence, democracy and reunification to this land.

South Korean unionists' struggle supported
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) - Employees of the hospital attached to Pyongyang University of Medicine met on Monday to express support and solidarity with members of the South Korean Federation of Hospital Workers Unions in the struggle for vital rights and democracy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
At the meeting speakers noted that many unionists under the federation of have turned out one after in the strike against the authorities' unilateral "restructuring," wage cuts and layoff from May 12, responding before anyone else to the resolution of the South Korean Confederation of Trade unions which declared the second general strike.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Their struggle is an expression of resistance to the U.S.  colonial enslavement policy and the IMF trusteeship as well as eruption of curses and wrath on the South Korean rulers, they said.  They expressed full support for South Korean health service workers in strikes, saying their struggle for human dignity and Genuine life is entirely just.

NDFSK will make enemy pay for blood of Kwangju Uprising
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- Chief Pak Kwang Gi of the Pyongyang mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) was interviewed by KCNA on May 17 on the occasion of the 19th anniversary of the heroic Kwangju Popular Uprising and made public a statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Kwangju Uprising in May 1980 was a great eruption of pent-up grudge and wrath of the people in the south who clearly realized the entity of the United States as a brutal colonial dominator and an expression of the ardent desire of the people to terminate the fascist rule of its stooges and live in independence, democracy and reunification, the chief said, and noted:   The uprising shook the colonial fascist ruling system to its very foundation and developed the revolutionary movement of the people in the south onto a new stage of anti-U.S. independence and anti-fascist democratization.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The United States must make an official apology to the people in the south for the Kwangju massacre and  discontinue domination over and interference in South Korea and the Kim Dae Jung group that is patronizing and defending the Kwangju murderers must be sternly judged by history.   The NDFSK and the people in the south will vigorously rise up under the banner of the anti-U.S., anti-fascist struggle and make the enemy pay for the blood of the Kwangju upraises thousand fold.

Japan's ulterior intention revealed again 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries a signed commentary denouncing Japanese high-ranking officials for taking issue with the DPRK again.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Some time ago, the chief executive of Japan in a joint news conference with the U.S. President talked about nuclear and missile "threat" from the DPRK and "suspected abduction". And during his stay in a foreign country a the leader of the Democratic Party of Japan prattled about the "suspected nuclear development" of the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The news analyst says:   Their preposterous remarks betray the ulterior intention of the Japanese authorities.
   The Japanese authorities never open their mouth without talking about the improvement of relations with the DPRK. 
However, they are now spreading the rumour about DPRK's "threat" and "suspicion" and thus revealing by themselves that they do not truly want the improvement of relations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   What is grave is that they intend to take the road of overseas aggression in  real earnest on the pretext of "threat" from the DPRK. Overseas aggression is the invariable ambition of the Japanese militarists.
   The Japanese reactionary ruling quarters needed a pretext to justify their moves for overseas aggression. It is the fiction of nuclear and missile "threat" from the DPRK on the lips of the Japanese reactionaries.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They are scheming to put a label of "terrorism" on the DPRK in a bid to impair its ever mounting greatness and external authority.
   No matter how hard they may resort to double-dealing tactics, the general situation will not change as they want.

KPA anniversary foundation celebrated abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- The 67th founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army was celebrated in foreign countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various events including celebration meetings, lectures, film shows and photo exhibitions were held in more than 50 countries including China, Syria and Guinea with the attendance of high-ranking military, political and public officials.    The events highly praised the immortal exploits of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il in building the revolutionary armed forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Special write-ups with portraits of Kim Jong Il were edited by more than 100 kinds of publications in more than 30 countries including India, Mongolia and Russia.        
Special programs were broadcast by TV stations of Cuba, Equatorial Guinea, Ecuador and other countries in the evening which gets of highest audience rating.
    Foreign radios broadcast Korean songs.

40-year long history of open-air theatre
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- The 40th anniversary of the Youth Park Open-air Theatre at the foot of Moran hill in Pyongyang was commemorated recently.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The theatre was built and opened on May 15, Juche 48 (1959) when the postwar rehabilitation was in full swing in Korea. It has 12,000 seats and a stage, rooms for creation, projection, fine art, sound conditioning, amusement and so on.   Since its foundation it has served as a base for extracurricular education and mass education where schoolchildren and citizens in Pyongyang train their artistic talents and skills to the full.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The theatre was visited by the President Kim Il Sung five times and General Secretary Kim Jong Il three times.   The President fixed the site for the theatre. After it was built he visited and named it the Youth Park Open-air Theatre. He established its orderly management system and sent to it educational equipment needed for extracurricular education.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il sent valuable educational equipment on seven times and guided a large-scale music and dance poetical drama "Songs of Loyalty of Youth Vanguards" performed by 5,000 schoolchildren and students in June 1971.
   Officials, creators and teachers of the theatre created over 7,000 literary and art works including eloquence, poems and songs befitting young people's mentalities to contribute to the education.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   More than 40 million young people and working people participated in multifarious political and cultural functions at the theatre.
   The staff of the theatre have trained students to be able men fully prepared mentally, morally and physically through vocal, oratorical, literary, fine art and Taekwon-do circles.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The theatre gave a great contribution to promoting international friendship and unity.   International events were held at the theatre on 42 occasions, including the 13th world festival of youth and students.

Self-proclaimed "people's government"  denounced
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- The South Korean self-proclaimed "people's government" rulers made desperate efforts to cover up their dirty colors by loudly talking about "achievements" during their tenure of office.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   More than 2.3 million people were investigated by public prosecutors in South Korea last year alone. Meanwhile, prisoners of conscience 4.6 times as many as over those in one year of the "civilian-veiled government" were put behind bars and over 6,300 people on a daily average were arrested, imprisoned and punished.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The fascist clique of self-proclaimed "people's government" mobilized over 20,000 riot police, helicopter gunboats and armored cars to suppress the demonstrations of people.
   More than 53,000 enterprises went bankrupt during one year of the self-proclaimed "people's government" rule.
   Commodity export value in February decreased by 16 percent as against the same period of last year, which was the lowest in 14 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Though the present ruling quarters vociferously clamored for overcoming the "crisis of foreign currency," the foreign debts at the end of January amounted to 176.9 billion dollars, an increase of 25.3 billion dollars over that last year.
   In a year after the appearance of the "people's government", the "defence spending" reached 13,749 billion won and the number of war exercises against the north increased ten times over that in the same period of the "civilian-veiled government".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The present rulers offered 390 million dollars for upkeep of U.S. troops in South Korea in the first year after they came into power under the cloak of "defence cost sharing". The amount is an increase of 36 million dollars over the figure of the previous year.
   The figures and facts fully reveal the dirty colors of the "people's government" which has been engaged in irregularities, lording it over the people.

DPRK's three charters of national reunification hailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- A lecture meeting on the three charters of national reunification was held in Georgetown on May 11 under the sponsorship of the Guyana-Korea Friendship Association.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Chairman of the association Samuel Soul, said that, badly pained to see Korea divided into two, Kim Il Sung, the eternal President of the DPRK put forward the most reasonable and realistic proposals to reunify the country by means of confederacy on the basis of the three principles of independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The great leader Kim Jong Il formulated the President's proposals on reunification as three charters of national reunification and made all efforts to realise them, he noted.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Secretary general Sonya Pasy stressed that the main obstacle to Korea's reunification is the U.S. forces' occupation of South Korea and the separatist forces of South Korea are suppressing the pro-reunification patriotic movement and democratic forces by depending on foreign forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He strongly called for an immediate withdrawal of the U.S. troops from South Korea and prompt removal of all obstacles to the reunification of Korea such as "National Security Law", "intelligence service" and concrete wall.

Anniversary of Kwangju Popular Uprising marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a by-lined article to the 19th anniversary of the heroic Kwangju Popular Uprising in South Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was South Korean people's resistance of justice and their massive armed uprising opposing the colonial fascist rule of the U.S. and their stooges and aspiring after democracy of society and national reunification, the article says, and goes on:   The Kwangju popular uprising was quelled mercilessly by the brutal armed forces under the manipulation of the U.S. However, it dealt a telling blow at the colonial and fascist dictatorial rule of the U.S. and their lackeys and gave great impetus to the South Korean people's movement for independence, democracy and reunification and the world's oppressed people's struggle for national liberation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Though 19 years have passed since the resistance, the desire of upraises who shed their blood of patriotism, has not yet been realized.   The bloody lesson from the uprising is that with the U.S. aggression troops in South Korea left intact, it is impossible for the South Korean people to free themselves from the yoke of colonial enslavement and to remove the danger of war on the Korean peninsula and realize the nation's desire for reunification of the country.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Students and other people in South Korea should vigorously wage an anti-U.S. struggle for independence to drive out the U.S. from South Korea and retake the deprived national dignity and sovereignty and anti-"government" struggle to wipe out traitors to the nation.
